beer.beer_description:
West Coast Double IPA

Our first double IPA.
Centennial, Nelson Sauvin, Idaho 7, Eclipse and Galaxy stack together like a dream tetris run. Just the right amount of malt sweetness and hop bitterness hold together our biggest IPA ever.

items.checkin_comment: A tropical driven double WCIPA that has a nice lingering bitterness and plentiful chest warming booze. There is no doubting the ‘double’ in this one but the tropical flavours keep you coming back for more.

items.badge_description: When a single isn’t enough, make it a double. Doubling the hops and malts in a recipe results in a higher ABV and can pack quite a boozey punch. That's 20 different beers with the style that contains Imperial / Double in its style name. Try 5 more for Level 5!

items.checkin_comment: Serendipity to score one of these after I thought I’d missed out a few months ago. Beautiful malts, absolute luxury and still has a refreshing citrus tickle before the clamp of bitterness arrives. A colossal brew from the usually more delicate MR crew.
